1.filling data the missing data in conlumn Ozone, I pick the average value of Ozone per month to filling the NA data, because filling NA value by average could reduce the influence of those NA value, which wont change the average acutal values.for the coding, I use for loop to raplce each empty value by average value.

ave_Ozone<-select(dataset,Ozone,Month)%>%group_by(Month)%>%summarise(ave=as.integer(mean(Ozone,na.rm = TRUE)))
for(i in 1:length(dataset$Ozone)){
  if(is.na(dataset$Ozone[i])){
    if(dataset$Month[i]==5){
      dataset$Ozone[i]=ave_Ozone$ave[1]
    }else if(dataset$Month[i]==6){
      dataset$Ozone[i]=ave_Ozone$ave[2]
    }else if(dataset$Month[i]==7){
      dataset$Ozone[i]=ave_Ozone$ave[3]
    }
  }
}
print(dataset)

2.grouping bar I decided using Month as x axis and type as filling colour, beacuse we can see each month the comparision ofOzone, Wind, and Temp, here we can get a conclusion is that each mouth the ave_Temp is largest and the ave_Wind is smallest, then for each group we can see that the ave_Temp and the ave_Ozone are increasing during 3 month while ave_Wind is descresing.

library(tidyr)
value_ave<-group_by(dataset,Month)%>%summarise(ave_Ozone=mean(Ozone),ave_Wind=mean(Wind),ave_Temp=mean(Temp))
tidy_value_ave<-gather(value_ave,key=type,value=outcome,ave_Ozone:ave_Wind:ave_Temp)
## Warning in x:y: numerical expression has 2 elements: only the first used
ggplot(tidy_value_ave, aes(x=Month, y = outcome, fill=type)) +
  geom_col(position="dodge", colour = "black") + 
  scale_fill_manual(values = c("red", "blue","yellow"))

3.Ordering group Ordering group is is using reorder function to merger two atttribute, first is a unique id of each month and type, another attribute is the value of average values.From this graph we can see the aver_Tep is much more greater than others for each mouth.

tidy_value_ave2<-mutate(tidy_value_ave,Id=paste(as.character(type),as.character(Month),seq=""))
ggplot(tidy_value_ave2, aes(x=reorder(Id,outcome), y = outcome, fill=type))+ 
  geom_col(colour = "black") + 
  scale_fill_manual(values = c("red", "blue","yellow")) +
  xlab("Month+Type")

dataset2<-left_join(dataset,value_ave,key="Month")

5.Slope Chart I used group_by and summarise functions to calculate the average for the month/3 month maximum value. After that, I use mutate function to add two new columns (class1 and class2), which contains two classes (red and green). Green is grow and red is decline.The result of the slope chart signs that the value of temp and ozone grow from May to July. The value of wind decreased during this period.Especially for the ozone during june to july,there is a big improvement,its from 0.2-0.4, other types like wind and temp have a slow improvement or decline.

#average is the average for the month/3 month maximum value
month_feature <- dataset3 %>% group_by(Month) %>% summarise(temp = mean(Temp)/max(dataset3$Temp),wind= mean(Wind)/max(dataset3$Wind),ozone = mean(Ozone)/max(dataset3$Ozone)) 
a<-data.frame(t(month_feature))
a<-a[-1,]
colnames(a) <- c("May","June","July")
a<-mutate(a,type=rownames(a),class1=(ifelse((as.numeric(a$June)-as.numeric(a$May))< 0,"red","green")),class2=(ifelse((as.numeric(a$July)-as.numeric(a$June))<0,"red","green")))
left_label <- paste(a$type,a$May,sep=", ")
middle_label<-paste(a$type, a$June,sep=", ")
right_label <- paste(a$type,a$July,sep=", ")

p <- ggplot(a) +
                  geom_vline(xintercept=5, linetype="dashed", size=.1) +
                  geom_vline(xintercept=6, linetype="dashed", size=.1) +
                  geom_vline(xintercept=7, linetype="dashed", size=.1) +
                  labs(x="Month", y="Mean Temp, Wind,Ozone")+
                  xlim(4.5, 7.5)+
                  ylim(0,(1.2*max(a$May,a$June,a$July)))


p <- p + geom_segment(aes(x=5, xend=6, y=a$May, yend=a$June, col=class1), size=.75, show.legend=T)
p <- p + geom_segment(aes(x=6, xend=7, y=a$June, yend=a$July, col=class2), size=.75, show.legend=T) + 
        scale_color_manual(labels = c("Up", "Down"), values = c("green"="#00ba38", "red"="#f8766d"))

p <- p + geom_text(label=left_label,x=rep(5, NROW(a)),y=a$May, size=3.5)
p <- p + geom_text(label=middle_label,x=rep(6, NROW(a)), y=a$June, size=3.5)
p <- p + geom_text(label=right_label, y=a$July, x=rep(7, NROW(a)), size=3.5)

p <- p + geom_text(label="May", x=5.0, y=1.1*(max(a$May, a$June)), hjust=-0.1, size=5)
p <- p + geom_text(label="June", x=6.0, y=1.1*(max(a$May, a$June)), hjust=-0.1, size=5)
p <- p + geom_text(label="July", x=7.0, y=1.1*(max(a$June, a$July)), hjust=-0.1, size=5)

This table is for generating distribution graph,there are totally 276 rows for values of Wind,temp,and zone,the type if the type names for different value, and moth and date for future using. firstly I use select to generate three signle tables of three different type value, and then using rbind to merge dataset row by row, finally add the vector of types to to dataset. for the median value, I add a new column for thw median through group by combine attribute(Month,and type). its for the meadian line for each different distribution.

dataset4<-select(dataset3,Month,date,value=Ozone)
dataset5<-select(dataset3,Month,date,value=Temp)
dataset6<-select(dataset3,Month,date,value=Wind)
type<-c(rep("ozone",92),rep("temp",92),rep("wind",92))
dataset7<-rbind(dataset4,dataset5)
dataset8<-rbind(dataset7,dataset6)
dataset9<-mutate(dataset8,type,combine=(paste(type,as.character(Month),sep="-")))
dataset10<-dataset9%>%group_by(combine)%>%summarise(median=mean(value))
dataset9<-left_join(dataset9,dataset10,key="combine")
## Joining, by = "combine"

6.Histogram this is about histogram, the x axis is the value of temp,wind and zone,the y axis is the frequncy of days for a certain value.I firstly generate the dataset of Month, value and type for total values, then generate this grap, this grap has 3 grids, its group by month,5,6,7 respectively, for each month, I got the different types value distribution, its for ozone,temp and wind by different color, so that we can clearly get the distribution of each type of value, the median line is the line of mean value, here we can got that the frequency days of wind almost follow the normal distribution in each month,and the zone in july has around 20 days value is 28-30, rest of those are distribute discrete.the temp is not much fluctuation for ythe tree month.

ggplot(dataset9, aes(x=value, color=type)) + 
  geom_histogram(binwidth=2,fill="white", alpha=0.3, position="identity") +
  geom_vline(data=dataset9, aes(xintercept=median, color=type),
             linetype="dashed", alpha = 0.5) +
  facet_grid(Month ~ .) +
  scale_colour_manual(values= c("blue","yellow","red")) +
  theme_classic()+
  theme(legend.position="top")

7.Frequency Polygon the frequency polygon is almost same to histogram, using geom_freqpoly to generate the graph, the graph is major represent by the ozone,temp and wind for each month in each faceted-grid, the first is the month 5 of different types values, the second is for month 6 and the last one is for month 7, for the wind, we can see month 5 and month 6 and month 7 have a simaliar distribution,and the ozone in month 7 in 28-30 has a very huge frequency, the temp is also do not have too much fluctuation, the frequcy of days and the range of values are similar.

ggplot(dataset9, aes(x=value))+ 
geom_freqpoly(binwidth=2,aes(color=type))+
  geom_vline(data=dataset9, aes(xintercept=median, color=type),
             linetype="dashed", alpha = 0.5) +
  scale_colour_manual(values= c("yellow","blue","red")) +
  facet_grid(Month ~ .)+
  theme_classic()+
  theme(legend.position="top")

8.Density Curve Density Curve is also represent the value of ozone,wind,temp of each month. there I use geom_density to generate the graph, the x value is values of three different type, in july, the ozone account for a very large range of values, its around from 0 to 100,in May and Jun, the ozone is smaller,its from 0 to 50. the wind and temp are simliar in three month, there are not too much fluctuation as well.

ggplot(dataset9, aes(x=value, fill=type)) + 
  geom_density(alpha=0.3)+
  scale_colour_manual(values= c("yellow","blue","red")) +
  facet_grid(Month ~ .)+
  theme_bw()
